## Quick start

This ZIP contains a `config.json` pre-filled from your canvas and a `src/agent.py` generated from your node configuration.

### 1. Initialize the DAB project

```bash
databricks bundle init https://github.com/veenaramesh/agentops-demo \
  --config-file config.json
```

This creates a full Databricks Asset Bundle project in a `{{{projectName}}}/` directory.

### 2. Copy the generated agent

```bash
cp src/agent.py {{{projectName}}}/agent/src/agent.py
```

### 3. Deploy

```bash
# Deploy retriever (if included)
{{#hasVectorSearch}}
cd {{{projectName}}}/retriever
databricks bundle deploy -t dev
databricks bundle run data_prep_job -t dev
databricks bundle run vector_search_job -t dev
cd ..
{{/hasVectorSearch}}

# Deploy tools (if included)
{{#hasUCFunctions}}
cd {{{projectName}}}/tools
databricks bundle deploy -t dev
databricks bundle run deploy_uc_functions_job -t dev
cd ..
{{/hasUCFunctions}}

# Deploy agent
cd {{{projectName}}}/agent
databricks bundle deploy -t dev
databricks bundle run agent_development_job -t dev
```

